  "name": "LED Fade-Off Circuit",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "LED Fade-Off Circuit",
    "description": "USB → slide switch → 1kΩ → split: 1000µF cap (center) and red LED (east) in parallel — no second resistor on the LED branch. Flip the switch on to charge both; flip off and watch the LED fade out over several seconds as the cap empties through the LED. Lesson 20 used a tact button and a 470Ω on the LED branch; here the LED sits directly across the cap for a smoother fade-off."
  },
